  "prompt": "What is the definition of current?",
  "response": "Current can refer to different concepts depending on the context in which it is used. Here are a few common definitions of current:\n\n1. **Electrical Current**: In physics and electrical engineering, current is the flow of electric charge through a conductor. It is measured in amperes (amps) and is denoted by the symbol \"I.\" The most common type of electrical current is the movement of electrons through a wire.\n\n2. **Water Current**: In hydrology and oceanography, current refers to the movement of water in a particular direction. Ocean currents can be influenced by wind, temperature, salinity, and the rotation of the Earth.\n\n3. **Air Current**: In meteorology, current can refer to the movement of air, such as wind or atmospheric currents.\n\n4. **Present Time or Situation**: In general usage, \"current\" can refer to something that is happening or existing now, in the present time. For example, \"current events\" are news and happenings that are occurring at the moment.\n\nEach of these definitions reflects a flow or movement of something, whether it's electric charge, water, air, or time.",
